Today is #worlddayagainsttrafficking.
We stand in solidarity to raise awareness against human trafficking in all its forms.

💙

Fact: Human trafficking is the fastest-growing criminal enterprise in the world. @timballard89

Fact: There are more people enslaved today than any other time in the history of the world-even when slavery was legal. @timballard89

Fact: There are 30 million slaves in the world. 10 million of those, are children. @timballard89

Fact: Human trafficking generates over 100 billion dollars annually worldwide. @timballard89

Fact: 17,500 women and children are trafficked into the US every year. @timballard89

💙

Want to help? Here is how:

Get educated. Here are some organizations that can help with that:
@ourrescue
@childrescuecoalition
@a21

Spread awareness on social media and in your community.

Report suspicious behavior. Here are some signs from @a21 that might help you spot trafficking:
•May be easily startled, agitated or afraid
•Unsure of where they are
•Unable to explain injuries or possessions
•May have strange markings/branding/tattoo
•Unexplained hotel use
• Accompanied by older ‘boyfriend’/companion
•(Children) dressed to look older than they are
Call 1(888)-373-7888 or text BeFREE to 233733 if you see any signs of trafficking.

