Today is WORLD DAY AGAINST HUMAN TRAFFICKING. I need you ALL to share, get informed and take action! 

@ninavee shared a video on her page (IGTV). 
We have been passionate about ending child trafficking for years, Nina had to talk about it on the lead up to July 30th, World Day Against Trafficking. Child sex trafficking is the fastest growing criminal enterprise in the world. Annually, the business of human trafficking globally generates $150 billion in profits. Millions of children are being exploited. It's our responsibility to raise awareness so we can find and rescue these children and end child trafficking. Human trafficking is a booming business that is being propelled by the powerful. It exists in so many sickening forms. It’s heart wrenching. We’re talking about children. Infants, 1, 2, 3 year olds. I’m talking about under 16’s. Children are kidnapped and trafficked by strangers. Children are trafficked by their own families. 

What can we do? Firstly, we can educate ourselves. The more we know the more we would dedicate our time to stopping it. There are various ways to help. Please visit the organisations linked below. You can share this video. Get loud on social media. Please help raise awareness on child trafficking and the importance of government action. Please share any revenant and helpful info in the comments section so we can help each other. 
To those who have watched this video, thank you. 

